# backend/requirements-dev.in — dev-time tooling dependencies.
#
# FX.6.7 (2026-05-04): peeled out of ``backend/requirements.in`` so the
# production lockfile (``requirements.txt``, consumed by Dockerfile.backend
# + every prod-shaped CI job) no longer carries test runners and lint /
# audit CLIs that the runtime never imports.
#
# The split:
#   * ``backend/requirements.in``  — runtime imports only (FastAPI,
#     SQLAlchemy, Alembic, asyncpg, anthropic, httpx, …). httpx STAYS
#     in prod because backend code (47 files: backend/security/oauth_*,
#     backend/email_delivery/*, backend/storage_provisioning/*, …)
#     imports it directly at runtime — only ``pytest`` / ``respx`` are
#     truly test-only.
#   * ``backend/requirements-dev.in`` — pytest stack (test runners) +
#     respx (httpx mock; no prod import) + pip-audit / ruff / mypy
#     (FX.6.5 lint/audit toolchain, no runtime import path).
#
# Resolution / install pattern (pip-tools constraint mode):
#   * pip-compile reads ``-c requirements.txt`` so any transitive dep
#     shared with the prod lockfile (e.g. ``httpx`` pulled in by
#     respx, ``typing-extensions`` pulled in by mypy) is pinned to the
#     EXACT prod version + hashes. No ``==`` / ``--hash`` divergence
#     between the two lockfiles.
#   * Dev / CI test environments install BOTH:
#       pip install --require-hashes -r backend/requirements.txt
#       pip install --require-hashes -r backend/requirements-dev.txt
#   * Production (Dockerfile.backend, openapi-contract job, backend-
#     migrate job, frontend-e2e job) installs ONLY ``requirements.txt``
#     and never sees pytest / respx / ruff / mypy / pip-audit.
#
# Regeneration:
#   pip-compile --quiet --allow-unsafe --generate-hashes \
#       --output-file=backend/requirements-dev.txt \
#       backend/requirements-dev.in
#
# (CI's lockfile-drift gate runs the same command and `git diff
# --exit-code` on the result; out-of-band edits to requirements-dev.txt
# fail the build.)

-c requirements.txt

# --- Test runners -----------------------------------------------------
pytest==8.3.5
pytest-asyncio==1.0.0
pytest-cov==6.0.0

# --- HTTP mocking (httpx mock; httpx itself is a PROD dep, not here) --
# Used by FS-series provider adapter tests (FS.1 db_provisioning /
# FS.3 storage / FS.4 email / FS.5 jobs / FS.6 search / FS.8 stripe-
# billing) — see docs/operations/codex-collaboration.md.
respx==0.23.1

# --- Lint / type-check / supply-chain audit (FX.6.5 toolchain) --------
# Driven by the FX.6.8 nightly workflow (`pip-audit` + `ruff check` +
# `mypy backend/security backend/agents`). No runtime imports — pure
# CLI tools. Pinned to latest stable on PyPI as of 2026-05-04 so the
# local ``backend/.venv`` and the future Actions runner agree
# byte-for-byte.
pip-audit==2.10.0
ruff==0.15.12
mypy==1.20.2
